<!-- Numbers & BigInt (Precision Pitfalls, Math, Intl NumberFormat) -->

<!-- JavaScript Number Basics -->
-JavaScript has only one numeric type: Number.
-It’s a 64-bit floating-point (IEEE 754).
-Range: ±(2⁵³ − 1).

<!-- BigInt – For Very Large Integers -->
-Added in ES2020.
-Represented by appending n.